{
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "title: \"Using Python, Plots, and LaTeX in Quarto\"\n",
        "format: html\n",
        "execute:\n",
        "  echo: true\n",
        "  warning: false\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "## 📌 Introduction\n",
        "\n",
        "In this post, we demonstrate how to use **Python code**, **visualizations**, and **LaTeX math** in a single Quarto blog post.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 🧮 Defining a Function with Python\n",
        "\n",
        "Let's define a simple quadratic function using Python:\n"
      ],
      "id": "d40d121d"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "def f(x):\n",
        "    return x**2 - 3*x + 2"
      ],
      "id": "6fee3718",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 📊 Plotting the Function\n",
        "\n",
        "We'll plot the function over the interval \\([0, 5]\\).\n"
      ],
      "id": "0542be88"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "x = np.linspace(0, 5, 100)\n",
        "y = f(x)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.plot(x, y, label=\"f(x) = x² - 3x + 2\")\n",
        "plt.axhline(0, color='gray', lw=0.5)\n",
        "plt.title(\"Plot of f(x)\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"x\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"f(x)\")\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.grid(True)\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "c6e60e0b",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## ✏️ Adding LaTeX Math\n",
        "\n",
        "We can write LaTeX equations inline like this: $f(x) = x^2 - 3x + 2$, or as display equations:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "f(x) = x^2 - 3x + 2\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "To find the roots, solve:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "x^2 - 3x + 2 = 0\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Which factors to:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "(x - 1)(x - 2) = 0 \\Rightarrow x = 1, 2\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## ✅ Summary\n",
        "\n",
        "This blog post used:\n",
        "- Python code to define and compute,\n",
        "- Matplotlib to create plots, and\n",
        "- LaTeX to format math equations.\n",
        "\n",
        "All rendered together beautifully in a Quarto document!"
      ],
      "id": "f6928af6"
    }
  ],
